In [16]:
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20, 16))
ax1 = fig.add_subplot(211)

filtered_holder_df = token_analyzer.holder_df.copy()
filtered_holder_df[filtered_holder_df<0] = np.nan

total_chip_cost_in_usd = token_analyzer.address_chip_cost_distribution_df * filtered_holder_df

address_balanceInUsd = token_analyzer.filtered_balance_df.groupby("address")["valueInUsd"].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).dropna()

cluster = pd.cut(address_balanceInUsd, bins=[-1, 5000, 20000, 50000, 100000, 300000, 1000000, 1e+10], right=True,
                 labels=["holder wallet balance <= 5000", "holder wallet balance -> (5000, 20000]", "holder wallet balance -> (20000, 50000]",
                         "holder wallet balance -> (50000, 100000]", "holder wallet balance -> (100000, 300000]", "holder wallet balance -> (300000, 1000000]", "holder wallet balance > 1000000"])


lookback_window = 36

(total_chip_cost_in_usd.T.groupby(cluster).sum() / filtered_holder_df.T.groupby(cluster).sum().replace(0, np.nan)).T.iloc[-lookback_window:].plot(ax=ax1, figsize=(20, 8))
ax1.set_xlabel("Date", size=14)
ax1.set_ylabel("Chip Cost", size=14)
ax1.set_title(f"The Trend of Chip Cost within Different Group ({token})", size=18)
ax1.legend(loc=2)
ax2 = fig.add_subplot(212)
token_analyzer.chip_price_df.mean(axis=1).iloc[-lookback_window:].plot(ax=ax2,grid=True,label='close price')
ax2.set_xlabel("Date", size=14)
ax2.set_ylabel("Price", size=14)
ax2.legend(loc=2)
plt.show()
